icient to\nexplain the low observed star formation efficiencies of GMCs. Finally, we show\nthat very massive clouds with steep density profiles - possible proxies of the\ngiant clumps observed in galaxies at $z \\approx 2$ - are more resilient to\nfeedback than typical GMCs, with $\\epsilon_{\\mathrm{min}}$ between 1 and 12 %.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Oct 2018 17:59:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-12"}
