 scalar singlets (from\nlightest to heaviest) are of four-quark, quark antiquark and glue contents. The\nmasses of pure pseudoscalar and scalar glueballs are estimated around 2.0 and\n1.6 GeV, respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Oct 2018 21:17:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-01"}
