e\nforces acting on the bunch constituents and the bunch as a whole. The coherent\nand incoherent tune shifts for an arbitrary bunch displacement from the\nmidplane are calculated in the framework of an improved linear theory, for both\ninfinite and finite parallel flat surfaces. Moreover, the developed method\nallows us to generalize the Laslett image coefficients $\\epsilon_1$,\n$\\epsilon_2$, $\\xi_1$, $\\xi_2$ to the case of an arbitrary bunch offset and\nreveal relationships between these coefficients.\n  Appendix C provides a brief historical background of the development of the\nmethod of electrical images.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Oct 2018 08:55:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 9 Jan 2019 21:35:29 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 13 Mar 2020 08:08:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-16"}
